Title : 2014 Commonwealth Games Marathon Course
Text : The '''2014 Commonwealth Games Marathon Course''' is the route around Glasgow city that will be used for both the women's and men's [[marathon]]s in the [[2014 Commonwealth Games]].

==The route==
The route was revealed by the games' organising committee on Friday 7 February 2014.<ref name="route">{{cite web |url=https://www.glasgow2014.com/press-releases/games-marathon-route-set-offer-athletes-best-views-glasgow |title=Games Marathon Route Set to Offer Athletes the Best Views of Glasgow |publisher=Glasgow 2014 |access-date=2014-04-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140424021233/https://www.glasgow2014.com/press-releases/games-marathon-route-set-offer-athletes-best-views-glasgow |archive-date=2014-04-24 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> The races will each make two laps of the course, which starts and finishes at [[Glasgow Green]] in the very centre of the city, and will run for 26 miles and 385 yards (42.195&nbsp;km). The route will pass many of Glasgow's best known landmarks, and provide free spectator access to watch the races.<ref name="route"/><ref name="bbc">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-glasgow-west-26085105 |title=Glasgow's Commonwealth marathon route revealed |publisher=BBC}}</ref>

